title: Lowest Domestic Credit Provided by Financial Sector
description: In 2023, Tajikistan's domestic credit provided by the financial sector was only 11.31% of GDP, indicating limited financial sector development.

title: Minimal Investment in Transport with Private Participation
description: In 2022, Tajikistan attracted just $4.5 million in private investment for transport infrastructure, highlighting a need for increased private sector involvement.

title: Rapid Growth in Final Consumption Expenditure
description: Tajikistan experienced a significant 14.33% growth in final consumption expenditure in 2022, reflecting strong domestic demand.

title: Low Unemployment Among Highly Educated
description: In 2016, only 0.24% of Tajikistan's labor force with advanced education was unemployed, indicating effective utilization of skilled labor.

title: Minimal Child Marriage Rates
description: By 2017, only 0.1% of women aged 20-24 in Tajikistan were married by age 15, showcasing progress in reducing early marriages.

title: Comprehensive Binding Coverage for All Products
description: As of 2021, Tajikistan achieved 100% binding coverage for all products, ensuring stable trade policies.

title: Complete Binding Coverage for Primary Products
description: In 2021, Tajikistan maintained 100% binding coverage for primary products, securing predictable trade conditions.
